DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       The dlpiping utility is used to exchange  network  traffic
       over  a specific DLPI network device in order to test net-
       work connectivity.  Each host on the network being  tested
       should  run  an  instance  of  dlpiping  in server mode to
       reflect packets from the other hosts.  Then an instance of
       dlpiping  in  client  mode  can  be  used  to send an echo
       request to  any  other  host  and  receive  back  an  echo
       response.   If there is no response within 15 seconds, the
       default timeout period, then the client assumes  that  the
       remote host is not functioning.

OOppttiioonnss
       The following options are available with the dlpiping com-
       mand: Specify client mode.  Specify server mode.   Specify
       the  DSAP  to  use  in transmitting and receiving packets.
       Specify quiet operation.  Specify verbose operation.   Use
       IEEE  802.3  plus  SNAP  encapsulation when binding to the
       SAP.

DDiiaaggnnoossttiiccss
       dlpiping in client mode returns 0 if the  remote  host  is
       alive,  1  if  the  remote host does not respond, and 2 if
       there is an error.

